# Documentation Style

> **Template**: Customize this for your project's documentation standards.

## Principles

1. **Minimal**: Only document what provides value
2. **Current**: Update or delete - no stale docs
3. **Scannable**: Use headers, bullets, tables
4. **Actionable**: Tell readers what to DO

## File Types

| File | Purpose | Update Frequency |
|------|---------|------------------|
| README.md | Project overview | When structure changes |
| AGENTS.md | AI context | When patterns/stack changes |
| Feature README | How feature works | When feature changes |
| ADR | Why decisions made | Once (immutable) |

## Structure

### README Files

```markdown
# [Name]

> One-line description

## Quick Start
[How to get running]

## Overview
[What this does]

## [Main Sections]
[Details]
```

### AGENTS.md

```markdown
# [Project] - AI Agent Instructions

## Quick Start
## Project Overview
## Tech Stack
## File Organization
## Key Patterns
## Common Gotchas
```

## Formatting

### Headers

- Use sentence case: "Getting started" not "Getting Started"
- Max 3 levels deep (##, ###, ####)
- Don't skip levels

### Lists

- Use `-` for unordered lists
- Use `1.` for ordered lists
- Keep items parallel in structure

### Code Blocks

- Always specify language
- Keep examples minimal but complete
- Use comments sparingly

```typescript
// Good - minimal, complete example
const user = await getUser(id);
```

### Tables

- Use for comparisons or structured data
- Keep columns to 3-4 max
- Align text left

### Links

- Use relative links for internal docs
- Use descriptive link text
- Check links work

```markdown
// Good
See [the setup guide](./setup.md)

// Bad
Click [here](./setup.md)
```

## When to Document

### Always Document

- Setup/installation steps
- Environment variables
- API endpoints
- Architecture decisions (ADR)
- Non-obvious patterns

### Don't Document

- Obvious code behavior
- Implementation details that change often
- Things better shown by tests
- Duplicates of other docs

## Diagrams

- Use Mermaid for diagrams (docs as code)
- Keep diagrams simple
- Include alt text description

```markdown
## Data Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[User] --> B[API]
    B --> C[Database]
```
```

## Maintenance

- Review docs when changing related code
- Delete outdated docs immediately
- Keep AGENTS.md as source of truth
